com.aeonium.javafx.validation

Class FXAbstractValidator<T extends javafx.scene.control.Control,A extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aeonium.javafx.validation.FXAbstractValidator<T,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The control base type
    A - The annotation type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NotNullValidator, NumberValidator, RequiredValidator, StringValidator

    public abstract class FXAbstractValidator<T extends javafx.scene.control.Control,A extends java.lang.annotation.Annotation>
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class for the validator classes: Each validation case for a control gets one instance of a validator.
    Author:
    Robert Rohm <r.rohm@aeonium-systems.de>

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        public abstract void validate(T control,
                              A annotation)
                       throws ValidationException
        Validate the current data and/or state of control according to the validation constraints annotated at the field. This method is meant to set the value of the isValid property - also before it throws an exception.
        Parameters:
        control - The control
        annotation - The annotation
        Throws:
        ValidationException - Throws an exception when validation fails. The message of the exception should be specific to the reason of failure.

      • validate

        public void validate()
              throws ValidationException
        An overloaded version of validate(T control, A annotation) that uses the referenced control and annotation - use this as default method to trigger validation.
        Throws:
        ValidationException - Throws an exception when validation fails. The message of the exception should be specific to the reason of failure.
